                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Raṅganātha temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Māṟavarmaṉ Vīrapāṇḍya.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The beginning of the lines in this inscription are built-in and therein the date has been lost. The available details of date are saptamī, Wednesday, Tiruvōṇam, which are insufficient for verification.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the grant of wet lands with the income from the taxes such as <hi rend="italic">taṟi-iṟai, taṭṭārpāṭṭam, kāśāyam</hi>, etc., in the village of Pallavaṉpaṭṭu in the Śeṟuvaḷūr-paṟṟu, as tax-free <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> by the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭavar</hi> of the place, for the health of . . . . . . Perumāḷ (king) for worship and various offerings to god Nāyaṉār Dēvapperūmāḷ set up in the temple of Nāyaṉār Paṉṟi-Āḻvār in Tiruppaṉṟikuṉṟu in Śiṅgapuram in Palkuṉṟakkō [ṭṭam] in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam by a person (name lost) of Rājarājapuram in the same division. It is stated that <hi rend="italic">Irugai-madavāraṇa</hi> Rājarāja Brahm[ā*]rāyan (see No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0253">253</ref> below) drafted the record under orders of the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭavar.</hi></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
